post_cb({"38126010": {"ParentId": "38125820", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>From \u00a78.3.6 in <a href=\"http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/wp/html/oct97/decl.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">dcl.fct.default</a> :</p>\n<blockquote id=\"so_38125820_38126010_0\">\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>For non-template functions, default arguments can be added in later declarations of a function in the\n  same scope. Declarations in different scopes have completely distinct sets of default arguments.</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not undefined behaviour. What you're seeing is mandated.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2015579", "LastEditorUserId": "2736233", "LastEditDate": "2016-07-05T12:17:35.103", "Id": "38126010", "Score": "14", "CreationDate": "2016-06-30T14:23:22.633", "LastActivityDate": "2016-07-05T12:17:35.103"}, "38125820": {"CommentCount": "6", "AcceptedAnswerId": "38126010", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "1291716", "CreationDate": "2016-06-30T14:16:36.870", "LastActivityDate": "2016-07-05T12:17:35.103", "LastEditDate": "2016-06-30T15:16:44.500", "ViewCount": "152", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Title": "C++: is function re-declaration a undefined behavior?", "Id": "38125820", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>Code:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n\nint f(int x = 0) {\n    cout &lt;&lt; \"x:\" &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; endl;\n    return 0;\n}\nint main() {\n    f();\n    int f(int x = 1);\n    f();\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><a href=\"https://ideone.com/qhRvS7\" rel=\"nofollow\">Output</a>(tested on g++ 5.1):</p>\n<pre><code>x:0\nx:1\n</code></pre>\n<p>My question:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Is <code>int f(int x = 1);</code> a declaration or definition?</li>\n<li>Is function re-declaration like that a undefined behavior?</li>\n</ol>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "1291716", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_38125820_38126010_0": {"section_id": 3255, "quality": 0.9523809523809523, "length": 20}}, "n3337": {"so_38125820_38126010_0": {"section_id": 3127, "quality": 0.9523809523809523, "length": 20}}, "n4659": {"so_38125820_38126010_0": {"section_id": 4013, "quality": 0.9523809523809523, "length": 20}}}});